nitpick: change to 
```python
        if which == 'facts':
            return '{0}/{1}'.format(
                super(DiscoveredHosts, self).path(which='base'),
                which
            )
```

hardcoding `'{0}/facts'` path will work in this case, but if you'd like to add some more paths in future, you'll have a lot of `if ... return` statements, 1 per each path. 
in the proposed approach you'll need to update only condition, e.g. `if which == 'foo' or which == 'bar'` and everything will work fine without any extra code.

